warning.simpara:
You can turn such a raw socket into a usual lisp &stream-t;
  using &make-stream;, but you should be extremely
  careful with such dubious actions!  See the &clisp-devel;
  mailing list archives for more details.
  Note that &make-stream; will duplicate the &file-des;
  (using dup),
  so you still have to &close; the original raw socket.

listitem.para:
A &structure-object-t; RAWSOCK:MESSAGE with the following slots: &varlist-table; addr a SOCKADDR.
iovec a (&vector-t; &ubyte-vec;) (&start-k; and &end-k; arguments are applied to this vector)
control a &ubyte-vec; flags a &list-t;
